# book-flip-showcase

A single-page app that showcases book covers and provides a realistic page-flip reading experience.

## Stack

- Vite 7 + React 19 + TypeScript 5
- Tailwind CSS 4 (oxide engine, `@tailwindcss/vite`)
- react-router-dom 7
- lucide-react for icons
- pnpm 10 as the package manager

## Scope

- Static, client-only SPA. No backend, no auth, no CMS.
- Book metadata is declared in a single typed module (e.g. `src/data/books.ts`).
- Cover and page images live under `public/`. Placeholders are acceptable for missing pages.

## Out of Scope

- EPUB parsing, DRM, annotations, or user accounts.
- Server-side rendering or API routes.

## Source of Truth

The full planning doc lives at `docs/plan-1.md`. When making product or architectural decisions, defer to that document and update it in the same PR if the decision changes.
